Using Personal Information
We use personal information for the following purposes, among others, to manage members, provide and improve services, and administer Flyff Legacy and related services
• Member management, including user identification
• User protection and service operation, including restrictions on use for members who violate the terms of service and related laws, prevention and sanctions for acts that interfere with the smooth operation of the service, including fraudulent use, prevention of account theft and fraudulent transactions, delivery of notices, preservation of records for dispute resolution, and handling of complaints.
• Analyzing service usage records and access frequency, statistics on service usage, providing customized services and displaying advertisements based on service analysis and statistics, etc.
• Marketing and promotion, such as providing event information and participation opportunities, providing advertising information, etc.
Provision of Personal Information
We do not provide personal information to external parties without the prior consent of the member, except in cases where the member has directly consented to the provision of personal information in order to use the services of an external partner, or where the obligation to submit personal information to the company has arisen in accordance with relevant laws and regulations, or where there is an imminent danger to the life or safety of the user and it is necessary to resolve it.
The period of retention and use of personal information of the recipient is until withdrawal of membership or termination of service, and other storage periods stipulated by the company's internal policies and laws. The Company entrusts some of the tasks that are essential for the provision of services to specialized companies in Korea and abroad, and manages them in compliance with relevant regulations so that the entrusted companies can safely process personal information in accordance with relevant laws and regulations.
