Period of Retention and Use of Personal Information, and Destruction
In principle, the Company destroys members' personal information without delay when the purpose of using personal information is fulfilled.
For electronic files, we use technical methods to securely delete them so that they cannot be recovered or reproduced, and we destroy printouts by shredding or incinerating them.
However, if we have obtained prior consent from the member, or if we are obligated to retain it by applicable law, we will store it securely and in accordance with applicable standards.
In the following cases, we are obligated to preserve information in accordance with related laws, such as the Act On The Consumer Protection In Electronic Commerce, Framework Act On National Taxes, Electronic Financial Transactions Act, and Protection Of Communications Secrets Act.
Retained items
Supporting legislation
Retained period
Records about contracts or withdrawals, etc.
